{"key":"processedPost-10427971","value":{"id":10427971,"first":10427320,"last":10428610,"when":1243751721,"utime":"05/31/09 09:35 AM","content":"A good pinset will dry out a substrate pretty darn quick.&nbsp; Pick up the tub and you should be able to get a pretty good feel for the moisture content by the weight.&nbsp; If necessary, pour a few glasses of water around the edges and on top, and a few hours later, pour off any excess.&nbsp; If the veils are tearing and the caps are opening when the fruits are small, it's 99 times out of a hundred low substrate moisture content.<br />RR","title":"Re: Why Are My Veils Breaking So Early? PICS","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}